The paper discusses machine learning formulations of inductive program synthesis, which involves using input-output examples to synthesize source code. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces TerpreT, a domain-specific language for expressing program synthesis problems, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses different inference algorithms for program synthesis, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
